description: A total cholesterol measurement is the quantification of cholesterol in blood, total cholesterol is defined as the sum of HDL, LDL, and VLDL.

label: polyunsaturated fatty acid measurement
description: The determination of the amount of polyunsaturated fatty acids present in a sample.

label: testosterone measurement
description:
is a quantification of testosterone, typically in serum. Testosterone is a steroid hormone.Testosterone measurement is used in the diagnosis of
precocious or delayed puberty, infertility (in men and women), ovarian tumours, adrenal tumours and pituitary disorders.

label: apolipoprotein B measurement
description: The measurement of ApoB in blood. Apolipoprotein B is a major protein constituent of chylomicrons (apo B-48), LDL (apo B-100) and VLDL (apo B-100). Apo B-100 functions as a recognition signal for the cellular binding and internalization of LDL particles by the apoB/E receptor, and is upregulated in response to enterovirus 71.

label: apolipoprotein A-IV measurement
description: quantification of serum lipoprotein A-IV. Apolipoprotein A-IV, encoded in humans by the APOA4 gene,  a 376-residue mature O-linked glycoprotein.

label: high density lipoprotein cholesterol measurement
description: The measurement of HDL cholesterol in blood used as a risk indicator for heart disease.

label: non-high density lipoprotein cholesterol measurement
description: The quantification of NHDL cholesterol in blood, calculated by subtracting the amount of cholesterol in the HDL fraction from total cholesterol and used as an indicator for cardiovascular disease risk

label: apolipoprotein A 1 measurement
description: Is a quantification of apolipoprotein A 1 in a sample. It is encoded in humans by the APOA1 gene and is the major protein component of high density lipoprotein (HDL) in plasma. Apolipoprotein A 1 relates to lower observational risk of coronary artery disease.

label: triglyceride measurement
description: A triglyceride  measurement is a quantification of triglycerides in some body fluid, used as a biomarker for cardiovascular disease.

label: estradiol measurement
description: Is a quantification of circulating estradiol a circulating steriod sex hormone.

label: obesity
description: A disorder involving an excessive amount of body fat.

label: diabetic retinopathy
description: A chronic, pathological complication associated with diabetes mellitus, where retinal damages are incurred due to microaneurysms in the vasculature of the retina, progressively leading to abnormal blood vessel growth, and swelling and leaking of fluid from blood vessels, resulting in vision loss or blindness. [NCIT: P378]

label: vitamin B12 deficiency
description: A disease characterized by low serum levels of vitamin B12, either inherited or acquired. [PMID: 16846473]

label: type 2 diabetes mellitus
description: A type of diabetes mellitus that is characterized by insulin resistance or desensitization and increased blood glucose levels. This is a chronic disease that can develop gradually over the life of a patient and can be linked to both environmental factors and heredity. [NCIT: P378]

label: eating disorder
description: A broad group of psychological disorders with abnormal eating behaviors leading to physiological effects from overeating or insufficient food intake. [NCIT: C89332]

label: iron metabolism disease
description: Disorders in the processing of iron in the body: its absorption, transport, storage, and utilization. [MESH: D019189]

label: diabetes mellitus
description: A metabolic disorder characterized by abnormally high blood sugar levels due to diminished production of insulin or insulin resistance/desensitization. [NCIT: P378]

label: gout
description: A condition characterized by painful swelling of the joints, which is caused by deposition of urate crystals. [NCIT: C34650]

label: mineral metabolism disease
description: Abnormal levels of minerals in the blood.

label: overnutrition
description: An imbalanced nutritional status resulting from excessive intake of nutrients. Generally, overnutrition generates an energy imbalance between food consumption and energy expenditure leading to disorders such as obesity. [MESH: D044343]

label: type 1 diabetes mellitus
description: A chronic condition characterized by minimal or absent production of insulin by the pancreas. [NCIT: C2986]

label: porphyrin metabolism disease
description: A disease that has its basis in the disruption of porphyrin-containing compound metabolic process. [MONDO: patterns/basis_in_disruption_of_process]

label: metabolic disease
description: A congenital disorder (due to inherited enzyme abnormality) or acquired (due to failure of a metabolically important organ) disorder resulting from an abnormal metabolic process. [NCIT: C3235]

label: metabolic syndrome
description: A cluster of metabolic risk factors for CARDIOVASCULAR DISEASES and TYPE 2 DIABETES MELLITUS. The major components of metabolic syndrome X include excess ABDOMINAL FAT; atherogenic DYSLIPIDEMIA; HYPERTENSION; HYPERGLYCEMIA; INSULIN RESISTANCE; a proinflammatory state; and a prothrombotic (THROMBOSIS) state. (from AHA/NHLBI/ADA Conference Proceedings, Circulation 2004; 109:551-556)

label: gestational diabetes
description: Carbohydrate intolerance first diagnosed during pregnancy. [NCIT: P378]

label: multiple sclerosis
description: A progressive autoimmune disorder affecting the central nervous system resulting in demyelination. Patients develop physical and cognitive impairments that correspond with the affected nerve fibers. [NCIT: P378]

label: anxiety disorder
description: A category of psychiatric disorders which are characterized by anxious feelings or fear often accompanied by physical symptoms associated with anxiety. [NCIT: C2878]

label: migraine disorder
description: A common, severe type of vascular headache often associated with increased sympathetic activity, resulting in nausea, vomiting, and light sensitivity. [NCIT: C89715]

label: central nervous system cancer
description: A malignant neoplasm involving the central nervous system

label: brain aneurysm
description: A congenital or acquired aneurysm within the cranium. [NCIT: P378]

label: peripheral nervous system disease
description: A disease involving the peripheral nervous system.

label: Headache
description: Cephalgia, or pain sensed in various parts of the head, not confined to the area of distribution of any nerve. [PMID: 15304572]

label: stroke
description: A sudden loss of neurological function secondary to hemorrhage or ischemia in the brain parenchyma due to a vascular event. [NCIT: C3390]

label: cerebrovascular disorder
description: A disorder resulting from inadequate blood flow in the vessels that supply the brain. Representative examples include cerebrovascular ischemia, cerebral embolism, and cerebral infarction. [NCIT: C2938]

label: bipolar II disorder
description: A bipolar disorder that is characterized by at least one hypomanic episode and at least one major depressive episode; with this disorder, depressive episodes are more frequent and more intense than manic episodes.

label: REM sleep behavior disorder
description: A disorder characterized by episodes of vigorous and often violent motor activity during rem sleep (sleep, rem). The affected individual may inflict self injury or harm others, and is difficult to awaken from this condition. Episodes are usually followed by a vivid recollection of a dream that is consistent with the aggressive behavior. This condition primarily affects adult males. (From Adams et al., Principles of Neurology, 6th ed, p393) [MESH: D020187]

label: bipolar disorder
description: A disorder of the brain that causes unusual shifts in mood, energy, activity levels and the ability to carry out day-to-day tasks. Often these moods range and shift from periods of elation and energized behavior to those of hopelessness and depression. [NCIT: C34423]

label: Ischemic stroke
description: Acute ischemic stroke (AIS) is defined by the sudden loss of blood flow to an area of the brain with the resulting loss of neurologic function. It is caused by thrombosis or embolism that occludes a cerebral vessel supplying a specific area of the brain. During a vessel occlusion, there is a core area where damage to the brain is irreversible and an area of penumbra where the brain has lost function owing to decreased blood flow but is not irreversibly injured. [PMID: 32054610]

label: mononeuropathy
description: Disease or trauma involving a single peripheral nerve in isolation, or out of proportion to evidence of diffuse peripheral nerve dysfunction. Mononeuropathy multiplex refers to a condition characterized by multiple isolated nerve injuries. Mononeuropathies may result from a wide variety of causes, including ischemia; traumatic injury; compression; connective tissue diseases; cumulative trauma disorders; and other conditions. [MESH: D020422]

label: late-onset Alzheimer's disease
description: This is the most common form of the disease, which happens to people age 65 and older. It may or may not run in families. So far, researchers haven’t found a particular gene that causes it. No one knows for sure why some people get it and others don’t.

label: hearing disorder
description: A disorder characterized by the partial or complete loss of the ability to detect sounds due to damage to the ear structures or inability of the brain to properly interpret or process the auditory signals it receives from the anatomic structures of the ear. [NCIT: C3078]

label: otosclerosis
description: Formation of spongy bone in the labyrinth capsule which can progress toward the stapes (stapedial fixation) or anteriorly toward the cochlea leading to conductive, sensorineural, or mixed hearing loss. Several genes are associated with familial otosclerosis with varied clinical signs. [MESH: D010040]

label: sleep apnea
description: A disorder characterized by multiple cessations of respirations during sleep that induce partial arousals and interfere with the maintenance of sleep. [MESH: D012891]

label: insomnia
description: A sleep disorder characterized by difficulty in falling asleep and/or remaining asleep. [NCIT: P378]

label: eating disorder
description: A broad group of psychological disorders with abnormal eating behaviors leading to physiological effects from overeating or insufficient food intake. [NCIT: C89332]

label: retinopathy
description: Any disease or disorder of the retina. [NCIT: C62601]

label: retinal break
description: Retinal breaks are full-thickness discontinuities in the retina. They can be classified into tears, such as horseshoe tears and giant retinal tears, or holes, such as operculated holes and atrophic holes.

label: depressive disorder
description: A melancholy feeling of sadness and despair. [NCIT: C2982]

label: mental or behavioural disorder
description: A disease that has its basis in the disruption of mental process. [MONDO: patterns/basis_in_disruption_of_process]

label: neuroblastoma
description: Neuroblastoma (NB) is the most common solid, extracranial childhood tumor. It is an aggressive pediatric cancer that originates from neural crest tissues of the sympathetic nervous system. [PMID: 32903387]

label: alcohol dependence
description: Physical and psychological dependence on alcohol. [NCIT: P378]

label: brain neoplasm
description: A neoplasm (disease) that involves the brain. [MONDO: patterns/location]

label: handedness
description: A better, faster, or more precise performance or individual preference for use of a hand, known as the dominant hand; the less capable or less preferred hand is called the non-dominant hand. Dominance typically applies to all tasks, but in rare cases may be task-specific (known as cross-handedness or mixed-dominance) Ambidexterity is the ability to do any task equally well with either hand.

label: ocular cancer
description: A benign or malignant neoplasm affecting the structures of the eye. [NCIT: P378]

label: bipolar I disorder
description: A bipolar disorder that is characterized by at least one manic or mixed episode.

label: Alzheimer disease
description: A progressive, neurodegenerative disease characterized by loss of function and death of nerve cells in several areas of the brain leading to loss of cognitive function such as memory and language. [NCIT: P378]

label: age-related hearing impairment
description: Bilateral hearing loss caused by progressive degeneration of cochlear structures and central auditory pathways, typically associated with the aging process. [NCIT: C116367]

label: headache disorder
description: Various conditions with the symptom of headache. Headache disorders are classified into major groups, such as primary headache disorders (based on characteristics of their headache symptoms) and secondary headache disorders (based on their etiologies). (International Classification of Headache Disorders, 2nd ed. Cephalalgia 2004: suppl 1) [MESH: D020773]

label: schizophrenia
description: A major psychotic disorder characterized by abnormalities in the perception or expression of reality. It affects the cognitive and psychomotor functions. Common clinical signs and symptoms include delusions, hallucinations, disorganized thinking, and retreat from reality. [NCIT: P378]

label: Parkinson disease
description: A progressive degenerative disorder of the central nervous system characterized by loss of dopamine producing neurons in the substantia nigra and the presence of Lewy bodies in the substantia nigra and locus coeruleus. Signs and symptoms include tremor which is most pronounced during rest, muscle rigidity, slowing of the voluntary movements, a tendency to fall back, and a mask-like facial expression. [NCIT: P378]

label: attention deficit hyperactivity disorder
description: A disorder characterized by a marked pattern of inattention and/or hyperactivity-impulsivity that is inconsistent with developmental level and clearly interferes with functioning in at least two settings (e.g. at home and at school). When present, the symptoms of hyperactivity are most often present before the age of 7 years. There are three recognized presentations or subtypes from most to least common: combined type, inattentive/distractible type, hyperactive/impulsive type. [NCIT: C97160]

label: glioma
description: A benign or malignant brain and spinal cord tumor that arises from glial cells (astrocytes, oligodendrocytes, ependymal cells). Tumors that arise from astrocytes are called astrocytic tumors or astrocytomas. Tumors that arise from oligodendrocytes are called oligodendroglial tumors. Tumors that arise from ependymal cells are called ependymomas. [NCIT: C3059]

label: nicotine dependence
description: Physical and psychological dependence on nicotine. [NCIT: C54203]

label: epilepsy
description: A brain disorder characterized by episodes of abnormally increased neuronal discharge resulting in transient episodes of sensory or motor neurological dysfunction, or psychic dysfunction. These episodes may or may not be associated with loss of consciousness or convulsions. [NCIT: P378]

label: Self-injurious behavior
description: Self-aggression. | All of these actions can be impulsive, compulsive, or planned.

label: retinal detachment
description: An eye emergency condition which may lead to blindness if left untreated. It is characterized by the separation of the inner retina layers from the underlying pigment epithelium. Causes include trauma, advanced diabetes mellitus, high myopia, and choroid tumors. Symptoms include sudden appearance of floaters, sudden light flushes, and blurred vision. [NCIT: P378]

label: obstructive sleep apnea
description: Cessation of air flow during sleep due to upper airway obstruction. [NCIT: P378]

label: narcolepsy-cataplexy syndrome
description: A type of narcolepsy characterized by excessive day-time sleepiness associated with uncontrollable sleep urges and cataplexy (loss of muscle tone often triggered by pleasant emotions). [Orphanet: 2073]

label: diabetic retinopathy
description: A chronic, pathological complication associated with diabetes mellitus, where retinal damages are incurred due to microaneurysms in the vasculature of the retina, progressively leading to abnormal blood vessel growth, and swelling and leaking of fluid from blood vessels, resulting in vision loss or blindness. [NCIT: P378]

label: intracerebral hemorrhage
description: Bleeding into one or both cerebral hemispheres including the basal ganglia and the cerebral cortex. It is often associated with hypertension and craniocerebral trauma. [MESH: D002543]

label: deafness
description: A partial or complete loss o f hearing in one or both ears; the level of impairment varies from a mild but important loss of sensitivity to a total loss of hearing. | An inherited or acquired condition characterized by a partial or complete loss of hearing in one or both ears. The level of impairment varies from a mild but important loss of sensitivity to a total loss of hearing. | An inherited or acquired condition characterized by the complete loss of the ability to hear from one or both ears.

label: Sleep Disorder
description: A change from the patient's baseline sleeping pattern, in the hours slept and/or an alteration/dysfunction in the stages of sleep. [NCIT: C3376]

label: major depressive disorder
description: An episode of depression lasting two or more weeks without an intervening episode of mania. [NCIT: P378]

label: hearing loss
description: A partial or complete loss of hearing in one or both ears. It is classified as conductive, sensory, or central. [NCIT: C35731]

label: age-related macular degeneration
description: Age-related loss of vision in the central portion of the retina (macula), secondary to retinal degeneration. [NCIT: P378]

label: brain cancer
description: A primary or metastatic malignant neoplasm affecting the brain. [NCIT: C3568]

label: macular degeneration
description: Loss of vision in the central portion of the retina (macula), secondary to retinal degeneration. [NCIT: P378]

label: narcolepsy
description: A sleep disorder characterized by a tendency for excessive sleepiness during the day which occurs even after adequate sleep in the nighttime. The persons who suffer from this condition experience fatigue and may fall asleep at inappropriate times during the day. [NCIT: C84489]

label: autism spectrum disorder
description: A spectrum of developmental disorders that includes autism, and Asperger syndrome. Signs and symptoms include poor communication skills, defective social interactions, and repetitive behaviors. [NCIT: P378]

label: dementia
description: Loss of intellectual abilities interfering with an individual's social and occupational functions. Causes include Alzheimer's disease, brain injuries, brain tumors, and vascular disorders. [NCIT: P378]

label: occlusion precerebral artery
description: Occlusion of a precerebral artery.

label: vascular dementia
description: A degenerative vascular disorder affecting the brain. It is caused by the blockage of the blood supply to the brain. It is manifested with decline of memory and cognitive functions. [NCIT: C34525]

label: spondylosis
description: A degenerative spinal disease that can involve any part of the vertebra, the intervertebral disk, and the surrounding soft tissue. [MESH: D055009]

label: emphysema
description: A subcategory of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). It occurs in people who smoke and suffer from chronic bronchitis. It is characterized by inflation of the alveoli, alveolar wall damage, and reduction in the number of alveoli, resulting in difficulty breathing. [NCIT: C3348]

label: cataract
description: Partial or complete opacity of the crystalline lens of one or both eyes that decreases visual acuity and eventually results in blindness. Some cataracts appear in infancy or in childhood, but most develop in older individuals. (Sternberg Diagnostic Surgical Pathology, 3rd ed.) [NCIT: C26713]

label: asthma
description: A bronchial disease that is characterized by chronic inflammation and narrowing of the airways, which is caused by a combination of environmental and genetic factors resulting in recurring periods of wheezing (a whistling sound while breathing), chest tightness, shortness of breath, mucus production and coughing. The symptoms appear due to a variety of triggers such as allergens, irritants, respiratory infections, weather changes, exercise, stress, reflux disease, medications, foods and emotional anxiety. [EFO: 0000270]

label: ureterolithiasis
description: The presence of a calculus in the ureter of the kidney; this is most often composed of mineral salts and proteins. [NCIT: P378]

label: testicular neoplasm
description: Tumors or cancer of the TESTIS. Germ cell tumors ( GERMINOMA) of the testis constitute 95% of all testicular neoplasms.

label: disease
description: A disease is a disposition to undergo pathological processes that exists in an organism because of one or more disorders in that organism. [OGMS: 0000031]

label: anemia
description: A reduction in the number of red blood cells, the amount of hemoglobin, and/or the volume of packed red blood cells. Clinically, anemia represents a reduction in the oxygen-transporting capacity of a designated volume of blood, resulting from an imbalance between blood loss (through hemorrhage or hemolysis) and blood production. Signs and symptoms of anemia may include pallor of the skin and mucous membranes, shortness of breath, palpitations of the heart, soft systolic murmurs, lethargy, and fatigability. [NCIT: C2869]

label: interstitial lung disease
description: A diverse group of lung diseases that affect the lung parenchyma. They are characterized by an initial inflammation of pulmonary alveoli that extends to the interstitium and beyond leading to diffuse pulmonary fibrosis. Interstitial lung diseases are classified by their etiology (known or unknown causes), and radiological-pathological features. [MESH: D017563]

label: corneal disease
description: A non-neoplastic or neoplastic disorder that affects the cornea. Representative examples include keratitis, bullous keratopathy, and squamous cell carcinoma. [NCIT: P378]

label: hematologic disease
description: A disease involving the hematopoietic system.

label: device complication
description: Any problem arising from the use of a medical device. [ NCI ]

label: iritis
description: Inflammation of the iris. [NCIT: P378]

label: osteoarthritis, hip
description: Noninflammatory degenerative disease of the hip joint which usually appears in late middle or old age. It is characterized by growth or maturational disturbances in the femoral neck and head, as well as acetabular dysplasia. A dominant symptom is pain on weight-bearing or motion. [MESH: D015207]

label: arthritis
description: An inflammatory process affecting a joint. Causes include infection, autoimmune processes, degenerative processes, and trauma. Signs and symptoms may include swelling around the affected joint and pain. [NCIT: C2883]

label: hyperthyroidism
description: Overactivity of the thyroid gland resulting in overproduction of thyroid hormone and increased metabolic rate. Causes include diffuse hyperplasia of the thyroid gland (Graves' disease), single nodule in the thyroid gland, and thyroiditis. The symptoms are related to the increased metabolic rate and include weight loss, fatigue, heat intolerance, excessive sweating, diarrhea, tachycardia, insomnia, muscle weakness, and tremor. [NCIT: P378]

label: nontoxic goiter
description: Sporadic enlargement of the thyroid gland that is not associated with changes in thyroid function or malignancy. [NCIT: P378]

label: respiratory tract infectious disorder
description: Invasion of the host RESPIRATORY SYSTEM by microorganisms, usually leading to pathological processes or diseases. [MESH: D012141]

label: chronic primary adrenal insufficiency
description: A chronic disorder of the adrenal cortex resulting in the inadequate production of glucocorticoid and mineralocorticoid hormones. [Orphanet: 101959]

label: congenital vitamin K-dependent coagulation factors deficiency
description: Congenital vitamin K-dependent coagulation factors deficiency involving multiple coagulation factors.

label: prostate disease
description: A disease involving the prostate gland.

label: fibroblastic disorder
description: A disorder that affects fibroblasts.

label: acute kidney failure
description: Sudden and sustained deterioration of the kidney function characterized by decreased glomerular filtration rate, increased serum creatinine or oliguria. [NCIT: C26808]

label: cellulitis
description: Inflammation of the dermis and subcutaneous tissues caused by a bacterial infection. Symptoms include erythema, edema, and pain to the affected area. [NCIT: C26715]

label: endometriosis
description: The growth of functional endometrial tissue in anatomic sites outside the uterine body. It most often occurs in the pelvic organs. [NCIT: C3014]

label: pelvic organ prolapse
description: Abnormal descent of a pelvic organ resulting in the protrusion of the organ beyond its normal anatomical confines. Symptoms often include vaginal discomfort, dyspareunia; urinary stress incontinence; and fecal incontinence. [MESH: D056887]

label: Epiphyses, Slipped
description: One of the most common adolescent hip disorders and represents a unique type of instability of the proximal femoral growth plate. Four separate clinical groups are seen: Pre-slip (wide epiphyseal line without slippage), acute form (10-15% - slippage occurs suddenly, normally spontaneous), acute-on-chronic (slippage occurs acutely where there is already existing chronic slip) and chronic (85% - steadily progressive slippage, the most common form).

label: thyroid disease
description: A disease involving the thyroid gland.

label: nephrolithiasis
description: The presence of a calculus in the pelvis of the kidney; this is most often composed of mineral salts and proteins. [NCIT: P378]

label: benign prostatic hyperplasia
description: A non-cancerous nodular enlargement of the prostate gland. It is characterized by the presence of epithelial cell nodules, and stromal nodules containing fibrous and smooth muscle elements. It is the most common urologic disorder in men, causing blockage of urine flow. [NCIT: C2897]

label: urolithiasis
description: Stone(s) within the urinary tract. [NCIT: C114688]

label: osteoarthritis, knee
description: Noninflammatory degenerative disease of the knee joint consisting of three large categories: conditions that block normal synchronous movement, conditions that produce abnormal pathways of motion, and conditions that cause stress concentration resulting in changes to articular cartilage. (Crenshaw, Campbell's Operative Orthopaedics, 8th ed, p2019) [MESH: D020370]

label: dermatitis
description: An inflammatory process affecting the skin. Signs include red rash, itching, and blister formation. Representative examples are contact dermatitis, atopic dermatitis, and seborrheic dermatitis. [NCIT: C2983]

label: Herpes Zoster
description: A common dermal and neurologic disorder caused by reactivation of the varicella-zoster virus that has remained dormant within dorsal root ganglia, often for decades, after the patient's initial exposure to the virus in the form of varicella (chickenpox). It is characterized by severe neuralgic pain along the distribution of the affected nerve and crops of clustered vesicles over the area. [NCIT: C71079]

label: eye disease
description: A non-neoplastic or neoplastic disorder that affects the eye. Representative examples include conjunctivitis, glaucoma, cataract, conjunctival squamous cell carcinoma, uveal melanoma, and retinoblastoma. [NCIT: C26767]

label: Rh isoimmunization
description: The mother develops antibodies against red blood cell Rhesus antigens. This may lead to potential fetal adverse outcomes such as anemia. [NCIT: P378]

label: respiratory system disease
description: A non-neoplastic or neoplastic disorder that affects the respiratory system. Representative examples include pneumonia, chronic obstructive pulmonary disease, pulmonary failure, lung adenoma, lung carcinoma, and tracheal carcinoma. [NCIT: C26871]

label: Nasal Cavity Polyp
description: A soft and painless polypoid mass that arises from the mucosa in the nasal cavity. It is usually the result of an inflammatory process. It may recur following surgical resection. [NCIT: C3256]

label: osteoporosis
description: A condition of reduced bone mass, with decreased cortical thickness and a decrease in the number and size of the trabeculae of cancellous bone (but normal chemical composition), resulting in increased fracture incidence. Osteoporosis is classified as primary (Type 1, postmenopausal osteoporosis; Type 2, age-associated osteoporosis; and idiopathic, which can affect juveniles, premenopausal women, and middle-aged men) and secondary osteoporosis (which results from an identifiable cause of bone mass loss). [NCIT: C3298]

label: radius fracture
description: Traumatic or pathological injury to the radius bone in which the continuity of the bone is broken. [EFO: 0003957]

label: skin disease
description: Any deviation from the normal structure or function of the skin or subcutaneous tissue that is manifested by a characteristic set of symptoms and signs. [NCIT: C3371]

label: glaucoma
description: Increased pressure in the eyeball due to obstruction of the outflow of aqueous humor. [NCIT: P378]

label: Dupuytren Contracture
description: A fibromatosis of the palmar fascia characterized by thickening and contracture of the fibrous bands on the palmar surfaces of the hand and fingers. It arises most commonly in men between the ages of 30 and 50.

label: chronic kidney disease
description: Impairment of the renal function secondary to chronic kidney damage persisting for three or more months. [NCIT: C80078]

label: sunburn

The lumps formed in the skin are hard, and have about a half inch across, with a dry and rough top that is often scratched open. The exact cause is unknown but some factors triggering PN include liver and kidneys problems, nervous and mental conditions and other skin diseases. Prurigo nodulares, in some cases, can be seen in other diseases such as lymphoma, chronic autoimmune cholestatic hepatitis, HIV infection, severe anemia,or a chronic kidney disease-related itching known as uremic pruritus. Treatment is very difficult, and may include corticoids, antihistaminic and other medication such as thalidomide and similar (Lenalidomide). In some cases, cryotherapy, photochemotherapy and habit reversal therapy for the itch-scratch cycle has improved the symptoms. PN can last for many years, and the itching is so intense that may affect all the everyday activities. [GARD: 0007480]

description: The volume of a parasubiculum. [AUTO: patterns/patterns/entity_attribute]

label: caudate nucleus volume
description: The volume of the caudate nucleus, a brain structure implicated in many common neurological and psychiatric disorders

label: depressive episode measurement
description: quantification of some aspect, eg frequency or severity, of depressive episodes in patients with mental or behavioural disorders such as bipolar disorder or clinical depression

label: social interaction measurement
description: Quantification, typically by a questionnaire, of some aspect of social interaction, such as engagement in social activities,  or degree of contact with friends and family.

label: grip strength measurement
description: quantification of the force applied by the hand to pull on or suspend from objects

label: IGF-1 measurement
description: Is the quantification of Insulin-like growth factor 1 (IGF-1), also called somatomedin C. IGF-1 is a hormone similar in molecular structure to insulin. It plays an important role in childhood growth and continues to have anabolic effects in adults. Levels of IGF-1 are known to increase in some cancers.

label: life span trait
description: The quality of a life cycle. [obo: oba/patterns/entity_attribute_part_of]

label: age at menopause
description: The age of onset of (human) menopause, the beginning of the first menstrual cycle in an individual

label: vitamin D amount
description: The amount of a vitamin D. [AUTO: patterns/patterns/entity_attribute]

label: cognitive decline measurement
description: quantification of some aspect of cognitive decline such as the rate at which it occurs or its severity, for example in patients with dementia or Alzheimer's disease. Cognitive decline is ususally assessed using a structured-interview protocol covering a number of standardised areas.

label: superior frontal gyrus grey matter volume measurement
description: quantification of the volume of grey matter in the superior frontal gyrus, usuallly through an MRI scan

label: Myopia
description: An abnormality of refraction characterized by the ability to see objects nearby clearly, while objects in the distance appear blurry.

label: Thrombocytopenia
description: A reduction in the number of circulating thrombocytes.

label: comparative body size at age 10, self-reported
description: Description of an individual's body size at age 10 compared to average, as reported by the individual.

label: family history
description: Family history is a form of clinicaly history specifically about relevant aspects of genetic preconditions or family member's clinical history.

label: sex hormone-binding globulin
description: A glycoprotein migrating as a beta-globulin. Its molecular weight, 52,000 or 95,000-115,000, indicates that it exists as a dimer. The protein binds testosterone, dihydrotestosterone, and estradiol in the plasma. Sex hormone-binding protein has the same amino acid sequence as ANDROGEN-BINDING PROTEIN. They differ by their sites of synthesis and post-translational oligosaccharide modifications.

label: Abnormality of the skeletal system
description: An abnormality of the skeletal system.

label: family history of prostate cancer
description: A reported family history of prostate cancer in one or more family members.

label: Abnormal circulating lipid concentration
description: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a lipid in the blood circulation.

label: Abdominal pain
description: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) and perceived to originate in the abdomen.

label: Hematuria
description: The presence of blood in the urine. Hematuria may be gross hematuria (visible to the naked eye) or microscopic hematuria (detected by dipstick or microscopic examination of the urine).

label: clinical history
description: Is an information entity about the material's (i.e., the patient's) medical record as background information relevant to the experiment.

label: Hypercholesterolemia
description: An increased concentration of cholesterol in the blood. [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR: gcarletti]

label: Colonic diverticula
description: The presence of multiple diverticula of the colon.

label: Oral ulcer
description: Erosion of the mucous mebrane of the mouth with local excavation of the surface, resulting from the sloughing of inflammatory necrotic tissue.

label: knee injury
description: Injury to a knee.

label: Hypoglycemia
description: A decreased concentration of glucose in the blood.

label: Moderate albuminuria
description: The presence of moderately increased concentrations of albumin in the urine, defined as and albumin-creatinine ratio (ACR) of 30 to 299 mg/gm (3.4 to 34 mg/mmol). [HPO_CONTRIBUTOR: Eurenomics_fschaefer] [PMID: 30571025]

label: Cleft palate
description: Cleft palate is a developmental defect of the palate resulting from a failure of fusion of the palatine processes and manifesting as a separation of the roof of the mouth (soft and hard palate).

label: Iridocyclitis
description: A type of anterior uveitis, in which there is Inflammation of the iris and the ciliary body.

label: household income
description: A demographic parameter indicating the amount of earning made by a family.

label: fall
description: A sudden movement downward, usually resulting in injury. [ NCI ]

label: eye inflammation
description: an inflammation in the eye(s)

label: nap during day, self-reported
description: Having a nap during the day, as reported by an individual.

label: encounter with health service
description: Reason by which a person encounters a health service; useful to classify cases when the encounter is due to circumstances other than a disease or injury. This may happen (a) when a person who may or may not be sick encounters the health services for some specific purpose, such as to receive limited care or service for a current condition, to donate an organ or tissue, to receive prophylactic vaccination (immunization), or to discuss a problem which is in itself not a disease or injury; or (b) when some circumstance or problem is present which influences the person's health status but is not in itself a current illness or injury.

label: Umbilical hernia
description: Protrusion of abdominal contents through a defect in the abdominal wall musculature around the umbilicus. Skin and subcutaneous tissue overlie the defect.

label: total hip arthroplasty
description: A surgical procedure in which the hip joint is replaced by a prosthetic implant, that is, a hip prosthesis. A total hip replacement (total hip arthroplasty) consists of replacing both the acetabulum and the femoral head.

label: seeing a general practitioner for nerves, anxiety, tension or depression, self-reported
description: Seeing a general practitioner for nerves, anxiety, tension or depression, as reported by an individual.

label: seeing a psychiatrist for nerves, anxiety, tension or depression, self-reported
description: Seeing a psychiatrist for nerves, anxiety, tension or depression, as reported by an individual.

label: Eczematoid dermatitis
description: Eczema is a form of dermatitis that is characterized by scaly, pruritic, erythematous lesions located on flexural surfaces. [PMID: 32412211]

label: total knee arthroplasty
description: A surgical procedure in which the knee joint is replaced by a prosthetic implant.

label: Back pain
description: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the back.

label: ease of getting up in the morning, self-reported
description: Ease of getting up in the morning, as reported by an individual.

label: suntan
description: An induced skin pigment ( MELANIN) darkening after exposure to SUNLIGHT or ULTRAVIOLET RAYS. The degree of tanning depends on the intensity and duration of UV exposure, and genetic factors.

label: Thrombophlebitis
description: Inflammation of a vein associated with venous thrombosis (blood clot formation within the vein).

label: cleft lip
description: Congenital defect in the upper lip where the maxillary prominence fails to merge with the merged medial nasal prominences. It is thought to be caused by faulty migration of the mesoderm in the head region.

label: appendectomy
description: Procedure to remove the appendix.

label: Tinnitus
description: Tinnitus is an auditory perception that can be described as the experience of sound, in the ear or in the head, in the absence of external acoustic stimulation.

label: diaphragmatic hernia
description: A congenital or acquired weakness or opening in the diaphragm which allows abdominal contents to protrude into the chest cavity; congenital diaphragmatic hernias are caused when the embryonic diaphragm fails to fuse. [ NCI ]

label: recurrent
description: Episodes of disease that occur in individuals who have already had the disease.

label: insulin resistance
description: diminished effectiveness of insulin in lowering plasma glucose levels

label: medical procedure
description: An activity that produces an effect, or that is intended to alter the course of a disease in a patient or population. This is a general term that encompasses the medical, social, behavioral, and environmental acts that can have preventive, therapeutic, or palliative effects.

label: dentures
description: Dentures (also known as false teeth) are prosthetic devices constructed to replace missing teeth, and are supported by the surrounding soft and hard tissues of the oral cavity. Conventional dentures are removable (removable partial denture or complete denture). However, there are many denture designs, some which rely on bonding or clasping onto teeth or dental implants (fixed prosthodontics).

label: Malabsorption
description: Impaired ability to absorb one or more nutrients from the intestine.

label: number of cancers, self-reported
description: Number of cancer occurrences in an individual, as reported by the individual.

label: Hallux valgus
description: Lateral deviation of the great toe (i.e., in the direction of the little toe).

label: health trait
description: The characteristics in health that a certain person has.

label: Hiatus hernia
description: The presence of a hernia in which the upper part of the stomach, i.e., mainly the gastric cardia protrudes through the diaphragmatic esophageal hiatus.

label: Abnormality of skin pigmentation
description: An abnormality of the pigmentation of the skin.

label: number of non-cancer illnesses, self-reported
description: Number of non-cancer illness occurrences in an individual, as reported by the individual.

label: self-reported trait
description: Characteristics of an individual that are reported by the individual, usually to medical staff, including via questionnaires, rather than observed or measured directly by medical staff.

label: Chest pain
description: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the chest.

label: number of treatments or medications taken, self-reported
description: Number of treatments undergone by an individual (including medications taken), as reported by the individual.

label: family history of breast cancer
description: A reported family history of breast cancer in one or more family members.

label: Inguinal hernia
description: Protrusion of the contents of the abdominal cavity through the inguinal canal.

label: Cholecystitis
description: The presence of inflammatory changes in the gallbladder.

label: Nasal polyposis
description: Polypoidal masses arising mainly from the mucous membranes of the nose and paranasal sinuses. They are freely movable and nontender overgrowths of the mucosa that frequently accompany allergic rhinitis. [PMID: 18728843]

label: deep vein thrombosis
description: The formation or presence of a blood clot (THROMBUS) within a deep vein in the lower extremity

label: male
description: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population whose sex organs contain only male gametes.

label: female
description: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population that only produces gametes that can be fertilised by male gametes.
